---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Thank you — Recverse"
  description="Your request has been received. Here is what happens next."
>
  <main class="landing-page landing-page--thanks">
    <section class="hero section">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Thank you</p>
          <h1>Your request has been received.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            Thank you for your message. We will review your request and get back to you with a sensible
            next step — clearly, structurally, and without generic filler.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/en/services/">View services</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/en/">Back to home</a>
          </div>

          <ul class="hero-points" aria-label="Next steps">
            <li>Your request is being reviewed</li>
            <li>Next steps are being prioritized</li>
            <li>You will receive a structured response</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-card">
          <div class="card-glow"></div>
          <div class="hero-panel">
            <p class="panel-label">What happens now</p>
            <h2>Your request is not just being passed along.</h2>
            <p>
              We review your situation, classify the request, and determine which next step is both
              realistic and useful. The goal is not more complexity, but a sound initial direction.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-alt">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-kicker">Process</p>
        <h2>What typically happens next</h2>

        <div class="steps-grid">
          <article class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">01</div>
            <h3>Understanding</h3>
            <p>
              We review your current situation, goals, and likely pain points.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">02</div>
            <h3>Assessment</h3>
            <p>
              We assess which next steps are sensible, realistic, and proportionate.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">03</div>
            <h3>Response</h3>
            <p>
              You receive a concrete response instead of a generic standard reply.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-kicker">Good to know</p>
        <h2>Important notes for the next exchange</h2>

        <div class="trust-grid">
          <article class="trust-card">
            <h3>You do not need to phrase everything perfectly</h3>
            <p>
              It is enough if the general situation is recognizable. The next exchange is exactly
              where complexity gets reduced and clarity gets created.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="trust-card">
            <h3>Only share sensitive details if truly necessary</h3>
            <p>
              Please do not send unnecessary sensitive information in follow-up messages unless it is
              already clear that this level of detail is actually required.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section cta-section">
      <div class="container cta-box">
        <div>
          <p class="section-kicker">Further reading</p>
          <h2>In the meantime, you can already get an overview</h2>
          <p class="body-large">
            On the services page, you can see which types of situations we typically support and how
            the overall collaboration is structured.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/en/services/">View services</a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/en/">Back to home</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .landing-page--thanks .steps-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .landing-page--thanks .trust-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>